    "headline": "Google signs classified AI deal with Pentagon, The Information reports",
    "summary": "Alphabet's Google joined a growing list of technology firms to sign a deal with the U.S. Department of Defense to ‌use its artificial intelligence models for classified work, The Information reported ‌on Tuesday, citing a person familiar with the matter.  The agreement allows the Pentagon to use Google's AI ​for “any lawful government purpose”, the report added, putting it alongside OpenAI and Elon Musk's xAI, which also have deals to supply AI models for classified use.  The Pentagon signed ‌agreements worth up to $200 million ⁠each with major AI labs in 2025, including Anthropic, OpenAI, and Google.",
